SIMPLE: circumduct
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumduct
<hw>Cir`cum*duct"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumductus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>circumducere</ets> to lead
around; <ets>circum + ducere</ets> to lead.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To lead about; to lead astray.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To contravene; to nullify; <as>as,
to <ex>circumduct</ex> acts of judicature</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumduction</ent>⟦br⟧
